					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3295047#post-4450932</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-3295047/heroic-spirit-alexei-belitrov#post-4450932</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 21 Dec 2019 02:07:24 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>rum-and-laughs</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5410943</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I liked it but I was kind of dissapointed. I thought that the idea of taking an existing SCP and to treat it like a servant was interesting. But, in my opinion (I am new to the wiki so take it with a grain of salt), I thought it would be cooler to take a servant and treating it like an scp. For example: describing Jack the Reaper's ability to erase memories of her appearance as an anti-mimetic ability. Or to describe contacts that the scp foundation may have had with organisations within the fate universe (like the church, the clock tower, chaldea).</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
